:;
In here, theres an example of interacting with the shell.  
We will just open the github meaningful repo
;:
set result = $"start https://github.com/Banaolf/Meaningful-Language" :: the set result is optional. $ followed by a string means executing a command from the shell.

if result isnt 0
    print "Something went wrong!"
else
    print "Opened!"
end
::unset result <- This is planned syntax, and wouldn't be needed but would be good practice.